{
 "name": "RPlog_Glowblue_Noodles",
 "title": "Glowblue Noodles",
 "summary": "Aboard the Caspian flagship Leviathan, the Sarian leader Crestian hosts an intimate dinner of homemade Glowblue Noodles and serrith bacon for Axel Vichten and the weary pilot Johanna, who arrives travel-worn and ravenously hungry. Between Johanna devouring her meal and Axel's gift of Ithorian wine, the trio turn to news from Hutt Space: the Hutt Moff Nasiri has offered to let them bring firepower in to eradicate the last major slavers, though at the price of consolidating his own power. All three are deeply skeptical of doing Nasiri's dirty work -- Axel scorns him as a failed Moff who leads nothing, Crestian distrusts his worthless intel and parading of his 'witch,' and Johanna argues that invading the resource-poor, hostile sector would gain little and stretch the fleet thin. Crestian's chief concern is stopping the alleged enslavement of Sarians, while Axel simply wants to hunt slavers on his own terms. The dinner becomes a frank strategy session weighing whether to act in Hutt Space at all, and on whose terms.",
